01:43:21.270 --> 01:43:21.280
when I

01:43:21.280 --> 01:43:24.870
get

01:43:24.880 --> 01:43:27.990
busy.

01:43:30.719 --> 01:43:32.629
That feeling of

01:43:32.639 --> 01:43:35.189
inadequacy has a lot to do with

01:43:35.199 --> 01:43:40.709
how I was raised,

01:43:44.320 --> 01:43:46.550
because I was abused as a child and

01:43:46.560 --> 01:43:50.390
it tried to make me feel inadequate. But the Lord has

01:43:50.400 --> 01:43:52.790
brought me so far from where I

01:43:52.800 --> 01:43:57.270
was. I feel like as

01:43:57.280 --> 01:43:59.910
I get in the word more, it's helped

01:43:59.920 --> 01:44:02.310
me a lot. It's just

01:44:02.310 --> 01:44:02.320
staying—it's

01:44:02.320 --> 01:44:05.030
not allowing the thoughts.

01:44:05.040 --> 01:44:07.270
It's just fighting the good

01:44:07.280 --> 01:44:10.870
fight of faith. On days whenever

01:44:10.880 --> 01:44:14.310
it's like that, I put Kathryn

01:44:14.310 --> 01:44:14.320
Kuhlman

01:44:14.320 --> 01:44:16.470
on or I

01:44:16.480 --> 01:44:19.270
listen to it, and it helps.

01:44:19.280 --> 01:44:22.390
It's like you're getting punched,

01:44:22.400 --> 01:44:23.750
and when you're getting punched, you

01:44:23.760 --> 01:44:25.990
don't succumb to it. You have

01:44:26.000 --> 01:44:28.070
to fight. You get

01:44:28.080 --> 01:44:30.229
even with what you're just saying right

01:44:30.239 --> 01:44:33.109
then about being abused. People don't

01:44:33.119 --> 01:44:34.709
know your story.

01:44:34.719 --> 01:44:36.470
A lot of people don't know your

01:44:36.480 --> 01:44:39.830
childhood and being raised—you were sometimes in a

01:44:39.830 --> 01:44:39.840
car for

01:44:39.840 --> 01:44:42.310
how many months without food?

01:44:42.320 --> 01:44:45.270
Yeah. Well, okay, so you want me to

01:44:45.280 --> 01:44:45.830
tell the story?

01:44:45.840 --> 01:44:46.870
You can say some of it. A lot

01:44:46.870 --> 01:44:46.880
of people

01:44:46.880 --> 01:44:48.790
need to hear it. You

01:44:48.800 --> 01:44:50.310
don't ever talk. So, that's what I'm

01:44:50.320 --> 01:44:51.350
saying. There's a lot of people who don't

01:44:51.360 --> 01:44:52.870
know your story

01:44:52.880 --> 01:44:55.430
about you and how you were raised.

01:44:55.440 --> 01:44:58.709
Your dad was a preacher. Yes. I

01:44:58.719 --> 01:45:00.870
was raised Baptist. No,

01:45:00.880 --> 01:45:03.030
not Baptist. Sorry,

01:45:03.040 --> 01:45:05.910
he was not Baptist. I'm

01:45:05.920 --> 01:45:06.870
Assemblies of God.

01:45:06.880 --> 01:45:08.310
He was

01:45:08.310 --> 01:45:08.320
an

01:45:08.320 --> 01:45:10.550
Assemblies of God pastor;

01:45:10.560 --> 01:45:11.910
that's a lot different.

01:45:11.920 --> 01:45:13.990
Yeah, we

01:45:14.000 --> 01:45:16.790
were too Pentecostal for that.

01:45:16.800 --> 01:45:19.910
It's late, but that is what

01:45:19.910 --> 01:45:19.920
he—I'm

01:45:19.920 --> 01:45:22.149
not laughing at you. I just, when you

01:45:22.159 --> 01:45:23.830
say Baptist, I was like...

01:45:23.840 --> 01:45:26.550
I messed it up. You're AG,

01:45:26.560 --> 01:45:28.470
Assemblies of God. Yes, Assemblies of

01:45:28.480 --> 01:45:30.310
God pastor. Well, they got a divorce

01:45:30.320 --> 01:45:31.990
when I was 11,

01:45:32.000 --> 01:45:35.189
but he

01:45:35.199 --> 01:45:37.590
had been abused a lot as a kid,

01:45:37.600 --> 01:45:41.510
too. So, he brought that. It

01:45:41.520 --> 01:45:44.310
just came in because they wanted a

01:45:44.320 --> 01:45:47.189
boy and they had me. My

01:45:47.199 --> 01:45:49.189
mom told me that she wished that I was a

01:45:49.199 --> 01:45:51.430
boy because that was what they wanted.

01:45:51.440 --> 01:45:54.390
So, I knew that from

01:45:54.400 --> 01:45:57.189
a small child. And then he was abusive.

01:45:57.199 --> 01:45:59.270
My dad was abusive to me. Whenever I

01:45:59.280 --> 01:46:03.590
was in church, I got pinched if I

01:46:03.600 --> 01:46:05.910
moved. If I said the wrong thing,

01:46:05.920 --> 01:46:08.229
I got spankings all the time,

01:46:08.239 --> 01:46:10.390
more than any of my other siblings. And

01:46:10.400 --> 01:46:13.189
just a lot of hard stuff like I

01:46:13.199 --> 01:46:16.070
don't really like talking about, but

01:46:16.080 --> 01:46:18.310
we lived in a car for a

01:46:18.320 --> 01:46:21.350
long time because my dad would

01:46:21.360 --> 01:46:24.709
just disappear. He got let

01:46:24.719 --> 01:46:29.270
go from his pastoral job

01:46:29.280 --> 01:46:31.750
at the Assemblies of God, and it

01:46:31.760 --> 01:46:35.189
really derailed him a lot, so it

01:46:35.199 --> 01:46:38.550
kind of affected how he acted even more.

01:46:38.560 --> 01:46:40.550
He didn't take any other

01:46:40.560 --> 01:46:42.870
job. So, he was at home a lot with me

01:46:42.880 --> 01:46:45.830
and my mom was gone a lot. I was

01:46:45.840 --> 01:46:49.189
abused probably the most out of

01:46:49.199 --> 01:46:52.550
my siblings, physically and

01:46:52.560 --> 01:46:54.790
verbally,

01:46:54.790 --> 01:46:54.800
but

01:46:54.800 --> 01:46:55.830
never sexually.

01:46:55.840 --> 01:46:57.510
Thank the Lord

01:46:57.520 --> 01:46:58.870
for that. I think He was

01:46:58.880 --> 01:47:02.070
definitely praying for me. So,

01:47:02.080 --> 01:47:03.669
definitely keep praying for your

01:47:03.679 --> 01:47:06.310
spouse—the

01:47:06.320 --> 01:47:07.910
one that you're going

01:47:07.920 --> 01:47:09.430
to meet, that God has for

01:47:09.440 --> 01:47:11.430
you. Pray for them because you

01:47:11.440 --> 01:47:12.790
don't realize that they might really

01:47:12.800 --> 01:47:14.709
need that,

01:47:14.719 --> 01:47:16.149
because I feel like that really helped

01:47:16.159 --> 01:47:17.910
me. The Lord kept me through

01:47:17.920 --> 01:47:21.030
all of that. We would have so many

01:47:21.040 --> 01:47:22.470
good miracles in the middle of that.

01:47:22.480 --> 01:47:26.390
As kids, we were homeschooled

01:47:26.400 --> 01:47:29.510
a lot, but my dad took us away from

01:47:29.520 --> 01:47:31.830
friends and family, so we

01:47:31.840 --> 01:47:33.910
weren't around anybody. When we

01:47:33.920 --> 01:47:35.590
went to places, I would get in trouble

01:47:35.600 --> 01:47:37.750
for saying the wrong thing or doing the

01:47:37.760 --> 01:47:40.310
wrong thing because I was a pastor's kid,

01:47:40.320 --> 01:47:42.629
so I would get in trouble behind the

01:47:42.639 --> 01:47:45.830
scenes more than anything. It

01:47:45.840 --> 01:47:48.149
affected the way I acted, the

01:47:48.159 --> 01:47:50.629
way I talked,

01:47:50.639 --> 01:47:52.950
it affected everything.

01:47:52.960 --> 01:47:55.590
When you're a child and you're in

01:47:55.600 --> 01:47:57.910
that delicate

01:47:57.920 --> 01:48:00.950
growing stage and you are dealing

01:48:00.960 --> 01:48:02.629
with so much of that, I didn't realize

01:48:02.639 --> 01:48:05.750
how much it affected me.

01:48:05.760 --> 01:48:07.830
But that was just a crucible. I think

01:48:07.840 --> 01:48:09.430
that's what a lot of you probably have

01:48:09.440 --> 01:48:10.870
dealt with. I mean, I know I'm not the

01:48:10.880 --> 01:48:13.510
only one. There's a lot of people who

01:48:13.520 --> 01:48:15.270
have dealt with childhood abuse, whether

01:48:15.280 --> 01:48:17.830
it's verbally, physically, or

01:48:17.840 --> 01:48:20.629
sexually.

01:48:20.639 --> 01:48:22.550
I know I'm not alone. I know

01:48:22.560 --> 01:48:24.149
there's people that have had it way

01:48:24.159 --> 01:48:27.910
worse than me. We lived

01:48:27.920 --> 01:48:31.270
in a car. We ate ketchup packets for

01:48:31.280 --> 01:48:35.189
a while, and a lot of different

01:48:35.199 --> 01:48:38.149
things. My dad would disappear. We

01:48:38.149 --> 01:48:38.159
bathed

01:48:38.159 --> 01:48:40.310
in the truck stop with a sink.

01:48:40.320 --> 01:48:42.629
We went to the truck stop and we

01:48:42.639 --> 01:48:44.790
would take baths in the sink.

01:48:44.800 --> 01:48:47.270
Sometimes we would go to a

01:48:47.280 --> 01:48:49.109
church and my dad would just

01:48:49.119 --> 01:48:51.669
travel there, and he

01:48:51.679 --> 01:48:53.030
would get in with the people and the

01:48:53.040 --> 01:48:55.109
pastors, and they would like him. Then

01:48:55.119 --> 01:48:57.270
he would get the keys or

01:48:57.270 --> 01:48:57.280
something—he

01:48:57.280 --> 01:48:58.709
wouldn't tell them—but we lived

01:48:58.719 --> 01:49:00.629
in the church. We lived in the back of

01:49:00.639 --> 01:49:02.390
the church. I remember

01:49:02.400 --> 01:49:03.830
they would all leave and he was

01:49:03.840 --> 01:49:05.510
pretending to lock up, and then

01:49:05.520 --> 01:49:07.990
we hid our stuff under a table at the

01:49:08.000 --> 01:49:09.910
church in the back. We would pull the

01:49:09.920 --> 01:49:11.590
stuff out, like blankets and

01:49:11.600 --> 01:49:14.229
stuff, and we slept there. For years it

01:49:14.229 --> 01:49:14.239
was

01:49:14.239 --> 01:49:16.870
like that, and then he would

01:49:16.880 --> 01:49:19.270
just disappear. I remember so many

01:49:19.280 --> 01:49:21.590
birthdays where he wasn't there, and my

01:49:21.600 --> 01:49:24.229
mom was trying to work a lot, so

01:49:24.239 --> 01:49:26.550
she was really just absent a lot.

01:49:26.560 --> 01:49:29.030
I kind of had times when I had to fend

01:49:29.040 --> 01:49:32.470
for myself and

01:49:32.480 --> 01:49:35.510
just a lot of traumatizing little

01:49:35.520 --> 01:49:38.390
things like that through my

01:49:38.400 --> 01:49:42.149
whole entire childhood.

01:49:42.159 --> 01:49:44.709
It really affected me

01:49:44.719 --> 01:49:46.790
in ways that I still feel like the

01:49:46.800 --> 01:49:50.790
Lord's bringing me out

01:49:50.790 --> 01:49:50.800
of.

01:49:50.800 --> 01:49:52.070
All that to say, I don't like to

01:49:52.080 --> 01:49:53.750
focus on all that, but just because

01:49:53.760 --> 01:49:55.990
y'all haven't heard that story—that's just

01:49:55.990 --> 01:49:56.000
the CliffsNotes.

01:49:56.000 --> 01:49:57.910
That's the

01:49:57.910 --> 01:49:57.920
CliffsNotes,

01:49:57.920 --> 01:50:00.470
but

01:50:00.480 --> 01:50:02.149
a lot of

01:50:02.149 --> 01:50:02.159
the

01:50:02.159 --> 01:50:05.669
stuff that she deals with is from

01:50:05.679 --> 01:50:06.310
rejection.

01:50:06.320 --> 01:50:08.310
Rejection

01:50:08.310 --> 01:50:08.320
is—and

01:50:08.320 --> 01:50:09.830
you're still getting through it.

01:50:09.840 --> 01:50:12.310
Yes. It's in layers. It feels

01:50:12.320 --> 01:50:15.270
like an onion. I will

01:50:15.280 --> 01:50:18.229
go, 'I forgive him, I forgive

01:50:18.229 --> 01:50:18.239
him.'None

01:50:18.239 --> 01:50:20.070
of my siblings talk to my dad,

01:50:20.080 --> 01:50:22.229
but I will talk to him. I

01:50:22.239 --> 01:50:23.669
talked to him on the phone, but then

01:50:23.679 --> 01:50:26.149
he'll just change his phone number and I

01:50:26.159 --> 01:50:27.430
can't get a hold of him

01:50:27.440 --> 01:50:29.590
still. But I forgave him, and that

01:50:29.600 --> 01:50:31.669
took so much work with

01:50:31.679 --> 01:50:33.109
the Lord, with the Holy Spirit,

01:50:33.119 --> 01:50:34.790
for me to even be able to get

01:50:34.800 --> 01:50:39.510
there. But it's layers.

01:50:39.520 --> 01:50:41.590
It's not something that

01:50:41.600 --> 01:50:43.830
happens overnight.

01:50:45.679 --> 01:50:47.590
You have to

01:50:47.590 --> 01:50:47.600
be

01:50:47.600 --> 01:50:49.750
in partnership with the

01:50:49.760 --> 01:50:52.390
Holy Spirit on a day-to-day basis. I

01:50:52.400 --> 01:50:55.030
rely so much on him and he'll

01:50:55.030 --> 01:50:55.040
say—just

01:50:55.040 --> 01:50:58.790
taking a lot of time to listen and

01:50:58.800 --> 01:51:02.149
not talk so much because I know a lot of

01:51:02.159 --> 01:51:04.149
times in the past,

01:51:04.159 --> 01:51:05.669
whenever you feel like you're just

01:51:05.679 --> 01:51:07.350
pouring your guts out to God and you're

01:51:07.360 --> 01:51:09.510
just talking and talking and talking,

01:51:09.520 --> 01:51:13.669
it feels like—I relied

01:51:13.679 --> 01:51:15.830
so much as a kid on making good grades

01:51:15.840 --> 01:51:17.189
because that's how I got my

01:51:17.189 --> 01:51:17.199
parents'attention,

01:51:17.199 --> 01:51:20.149
so it taught me to be

01:51:20.159 --> 01:51:21.750
more

01:51:21.750 --> 01:51:21.760
sense-ruled.

01:51:21.760 --> 01:51:24.790
Thinking using intelligence

01:51:24.800 --> 01:51:27.669
instead of—because I saw in the spirit

01:51:27.679 --> 01:51:30.070
as a kid and my dad one time freaked out

01:51:30.080 --> 01:51:33.430
on me because I said I was

01:51:33.440 --> 01:51:35.270
talking to an angel, and he was like, 'Well,

01:51:35.280 --> 01:51:37.430
what was it saying? Don't

01:51:37.440 --> 01:51:39.270
ever do that again.'So it made me

01:51:39.280 --> 01:51:41.990
question a lot of things. All of

01:51:42.000 --> 01:51:44.390
those things combined, and having a

01:51:44.400 --> 01:51:46.070
bad relationship with my dad, has

01:51:46.080 --> 01:51:48.470
really affected how I have

01:51:48.480 --> 01:51:50.470
had to work at having a relationship

01:51:50.480 --> 01:51:52.470
with God. I know

01:51:52.480 --> 01:51:53.990
there's a lot of people out here that

01:51:54.000 --> 01:51:55.750
have had bad relationships with

01:51:55.760 --> 01:51:59.030
parents, or an absent dad,

01:51:59.040 --> 01:52:02.550
orphans and all of that. When you don't

01:52:02.560 --> 01:52:04.950
have a good father, or one

01:52:04.960 --> 01:52:07.910
that's there or one

01:52:07.910 --> 01:52:07.920
that

01:52:07.920 --> 01:52:10.390
you're able to talk to, it

01:52:10.400 --> 01:52:12.550
does affect your relationship with God.

01:52:12.560 --> 01:52:14.870
It affects how you can come to him

01:52:14.880 --> 01:52:16.550
because when your earthly

01:52:16.560 --> 01:52:19.350
father is gone or he's never there,

01:52:19.360 --> 01:52:21.350
or he says, 'I'll come to your

01:52:21.350 --> 01:52:21.360
birthday,'but

01:52:21.360 --> 01:52:23.669
then he never comes, you

01:52:23.679 --> 01:52:26.229
have that expectation,

01:52:26.239 --> 01:52:28.709
especially when you're a child, that it

01:52:28.719 --> 01:52:30.790
affects you and how you view your

01:52:30.800 --> 01:52:33.109
relationship with God. And then after

01:52:33.119 --> 01:52:37.109
Megan got diagnosed and all of that,

01:52:37.119 --> 01:52:40.950
it really just takes away

01:52:40.960 --> 01:52:43.270
that trust. It tries to affect that

01:52:43.280 --> 01:52:45.830
trust that you've trusted him. Lord, I

01:52:45.840 --> 01:52:48.310
trust you. And so I had to just

01:52:48.320 --> 01:52:49.990
come to the point where I was like, 'God,

01:52:50.000 --> 01:52:52.390
I don't feel like I can completely

01:52:52.400 --> 01:52:55.189
trust you. I want to; I need you to help

01:52:55.199 --> 01:52:58.390
me to get there.'And so doing that and

01:52:58.400 --> 01:52:59.990
just pouring my guts out to him every

01:53:00.000 --> 01:53:02.550
day, he'll say, 'Diana, do

01:53:02.550 --> 01:53:02.560
this'in

01:53:02.560 --> 01:53:05.750
these little things. But

01:53:05.760 --> 01:53:09.430
a lot of times when you're

01:53:09.430 --> 01:53:09.440
sin-ruled,

01:53:09.440 --> 01:53:12.550
you think, 'I have to... if it

01:53:12.560 --> 01:53:15.109
doesn't happen this way...'You feel

01:53:15.119 --> 01:53:17.030
like, 'I have to do this to make God

01:53:17.040 --> 01:53:18.550
accept me'because that's the way my

01:53:18.560 --> 01:53:20.229
parents were. With my earthly parents, I had

01:53:20.239 --> 01:53:22.470
to make good grades for them to accept

01:53:22.480 --> 01:53:24.950
me. So you feel like you have to do this

01:53:24.960 --> 01:53:28.149
much prayer, this much time,

01:53:28.719 --> 01:53:31.189
this much work to get there. And then if

01:53:31.199 --> 01:53:33.189
I do this, then he looks at me. If I fast

01:53:33.189 --> 01:53:33.199
for

01:53:33.199 --> 01:53:35.830
five hours a day, or if I fast for

01:53:35.830 --> 01:53:35.840
a

01:53:35.840 --> 01:53:39.270
month—however

01:53:39.280 --> 01:53:41.589
long it

01:53:41.589 --> 01:53:41.599
is—if

01:53:41.599 --> 01:53:44.550
I read an X amount of time

01:53:44.560 --> 01:53:46.950
to the point where it

01:53:46.960 --> 01:53:48.950
becomes where I think a lot of

01:53:48.960 --> 01:53:51.510
believers get to that point where

01:53:51.520 --> 01:53:53.750
you feel like you have to earn God's

01:53:53.760 --> 01:53:54.629
favor,

01:53:54.639 --> 01:53:55.109
right?

01:53:55.119 --> 01:53:58.070
You have to earn God's anointing. You

01:53:58.080 --> 01:54:01.270
have to earn God's hand on your

01:54:01.280 --> 01:54:03.750
life. But it's by grace. And that's

01:54:03.760 --> 01:54:06.070
why I try to tell her all the time: you

01:54:06.080 --> 01:54:07.350
don't have to do anything for God to

01:54:07.360 --> 01:54:09.270
love you. He already loves you.

01:54:09.280 --> 01:54:10.709
He already died for you. And that's why

01:54:10.719 --> 01:54:12.470
I tell her all the time, no matter how

01:54:12.480 --> 01:54:14.950
much you went through high school and

01:54:14.960 --> 01:54:18.070
college with a 4.0 and graduated summa

01:54:18.070 --> 01:54:18.080
cum laude,

01:54:18.080 --> 01:54:21.270
and you were brilliant. It was

01:54:21.280 --> 01:54:24.550
always her way of having

01:54:24.560 --> 01:54:27.350
people approve of her, of being the best

01:54:27.360 --> 01:54:29.430
that she was because she was the top of

01:54:29.440 --> 01:54:30.550
her class.

01:54:30.560 --> 01:54:32.550
But I've told her there's nothing

01:54:32.560 --> 01:54:34.070
you can do

01:54:34.080 --> 01:54:35.990
to get God to love you more than he

01:54:36.000 --> 01:54:37.510
already does.

01:54:37.520 --> 01:54:39.510
And that's what I felt like I had to do

01:54:39.520 --> 01:54:41.510
in order to gain their

01:54:41.520 --> 01:54:43.750
attention. I

01:54:43.760 --> 01:54:45.910
felt like I had to do that. So it

01:54:45.920 --> 01:54:48.550
taught me to be more sin-ruled than

01:54:48.560 --> 01:54:50.950
faith-ruled,

01:54:50.960 --> 01:54:54.470
to do more

01:54:54.480 --> 01:54:56.629
works. And that's what comes

01:54:56.639 --> 01:54:58.470
with the relationship of

01:54:58.480 --> 01:55:00.950
the Lord, thinking that a lot of

01:55:00.960 --> 01:55:03.589
believers think, 'Well, if I fast five

01:55:03.599 --> 01:55:05.350
days

01:55:05.360 --> 01:55:09.830
a week or read 20

01:55:09.840 --> 01:55:12.790
chapters a week in my Bible, maybe I'll

01:55:12.800 --> 01:55:14.629
have a little bit more anointing on

01:55:14.639 --> 01:55:16.870
my life to do

01:55:16.870 --> 01:55:16.880
something.'But

01:55:16.880 --> 01:55:19.270
it's all by grace.

01:55:19.280 --> 01:55:21.189
There's nothing you can do to get God to

01:55:21.199 --> 01:55:22.790
love you anymore.

01:55:22.800 --> 01:55:24.950
He already loves you unconditionally.

01:55:24.960 --> 01:55:27.910
It's how we yield to him.

01:55:27.920 --> 01:55:30.550
'Father, I give more to

01:55:30.550 --> 01:55:30.560
you.'That's

01:55:30.560 --> 01:55:32.310
what I tell her all the time, feeling

01:55:32.320 --> 01:55:35.270
inadequate from that abuse as a father,

01:55:35.280 --> 01:55:36.870
thinking... and then when Megan got

01:55:36.880 --> 01:55:39.750
diagnosed, it derailed Diana. I'm going

01:55:39.750 --> 01:55:39.760
to

01:55:39.760 --> 01:55:41.669
tell you all,

01:55:41.679 --> 01:55:45.830
at that time—what was it, 20 years

01:55:45.840 --> 01:55:47.990
ago?—I

01:55:48.000 --> 01:55:50.229
didn't think she was going to come

01:55:50.239 --> 01:55:52.149
out of it.

01:55:52.159 --> 01:55:53.830
At that time, when I was in the marriage,

01:55:53.840 --> 01:55:58.790
it was the darkest I've ever seen her

01:55:58.800 --> 01:56:01.589
of any human. It was awful. After

01:56:01.599 --> 01:56:03.350
her dad and all that, I thought,

01:56:03.360 --> 01:56:05.750
'Man, our life is starting out. We got

01:56:05.760 --> 01:56:07.350
married. Everything's great.'And when

01:56:07.360 --> 01:56:09.910
Megan got diagnosed with autism and they

01:56:09.920 --> 01:56:11.350
told her that she would never come out

01:56:11.360 --> 01:56:13.830
of a five-year-old level, that for the

01:56:13.840 --> 01:56:16.229
rest of her life she'll probably be

01:56:16.229 --> 01:56:16.239
at

01:56:16.239 --> 01:56:17.109
an

01:56:17.109 --> 01:56:17.119
18-month

01:56:17.119 --> 01:56:17.910
level

01:56:17.920 --> 01:56:21.510
mentally. And that was

01:56:21.520 --> 01:56:23.990
the darkest hour for me. I just thought

01:56:24.000 --> 01:56:26.470
there's no way our marriage is going to

01:56:26.480 --> 01:56:28.070
make this. That's what I thought in the

01:56:28.080 --> 01:56:30.229
natural because of how much depression

01:56:30.239 --> 01:56:32.070
she overcame

01:56:32.080 --> 01:56:34.310
and then pulling ourselves out of this and

01:56:34.320 --> 01:56:36.149
getting over it and being able to say,

01:56:36.159 --> 01:56:38.870
'God, I trust you even through this

01:56:38.880 --> 01:56:39.350
storm.'And

01:56:39.360 --> 01:56:41.830
that whole thing

01:56:41.840 --> 01:56:44.950
started another spiral of

01:56:44.960 --> 01:56:48.470
blaming. Because when I was a

01:56:48.480 --> 01:56:51.030
kid, it was, 'Who did this? You're

01:56:51.030 --> 01:56:51.040
wrong.'You

01:56:51.040 --> 01:56:52.629
get a spanking, and whoever did

01:56:52.639 --> 01:56:55.350
this wrong is... and because

01:56:55.360 --> 01:56:58.629
of the abuse and stuff, I had a big

01:56:58.639 --> 01:57:00.470
problem with who's to blame. Whose fault

01:57:00.480 --> 01:57:02.790
is it? So I blamed myself because I'm

01:57:02.800 --> 01:57:04.870
the mother. The buck stops here. It's my

01:57:04.880 --> 01:57:06.950
fault. But I couldn't find out what

01:57:06.960 --> 01:57:08.950
I did wrong. I did everything I was

01:57:08.960 --> 01:57:09.750
supposed to do.

01:57:09.760 --> 01:57:12.070
'It's my fault Megan's this way.

01:57:12.080 --> 01:57:14.149
I did everything I was supposed to do. I

01:57:14.159 --> 01:57:17.350
never drank. I never did any drugs.

01:57:17.360 --> 01:57:19.189
I didn't do anything wrong the whole

01:57:19.199 --> 01:57:22.470
time. No sin at all.'So I

01:57:22.480 --> 01:57:24.550
thought, 'Well, maybe I should

01:57:24.560 --> 01:57:26.629
have cleaned up my diet better. Maybe I

01:57:26.639 --> 01:57:28.870
ate something.'It was little things,

01:57:28.880 --> 01:57:30.950
stupid things, but those are the things

01:57:30.960 --> 01:57:33.189
that kind of tried to wedge in there

01:57:33.199 --> 01:57:35.030
that the enemy tries to bring

01:57:35.040 --> 01:57:37.270
to

01:57:37.280 --> 01:57:39.750
derail you. And so that's just what I

01:57:39.760 --> 01:57:41.270
went through.

01:57:41.280 --> 01:57:44.470
And I think that's why I try, even with

01:57:44.480 --> 01:57:46.149
the inadequacy of doing this

01:57:46.149 --> 01:57:46.159
channel—it

01:57:46.159 --> 01:57:49.270
tries to wear on you

01:57:49.270 --> 01:57:49.280
and me

01:57:49.280 --> 01:57:51.510
still to feel like,

01:57:51.520 --> 01:57:53.189
'What has God called us to do?'Do we feel

01:57:53.199 --> 01:57:55.030
that we can talk in front of millions of

01:57:55.040 --> 01:57:57.750
people? It tries to bring that

01:57:57.760 --> 01:57:59.430
self-doubt

01:57:59.440 --> 01:58:00.950
of what God's called you to do. And

01:58:00.960 --> 01:58:02.629
that's why I try to be real with y'all.

01:58:02.639 --> 01:58:04.950
It's a lot of pressure. And

01:58:04.960 --> 01:58:05.990
that's why I say I'm not here to

01:58:06.000 --> 01:58:06.790
perform.

01:58:07.199 --> 01:58:09.030
I'm just being me. And if I

01:58:09.040 --> 01:58:11.189
wasn't praying in front of you all, I'm

01:58:11.199 --> 01:58:13.109
going to be praying all the time

01:58:13.119 --> 01:58:14.550
anyway. That's what we do. So I just

01:58:14.560 --> 01:58:16.470
try to make it public and I try to

01:58:16.480 --> 01:58:20.390
really cut out all the spiritual

01:58:20.400 --> 01:58:24.229
celebrity performance, the major TV

01:58:24.239 --> 01:58:26.870
networks, the people that have

01:58:26.880 --> 01:58:28.709
huge ministries. I don't try

01:58:28.719 --> 01:58:31.510
to be the stereotype of this. I just go,

01:58:31.520 --> 01:58:33.669
'I'm just normal. I'm Brandon and Diana.

01:58:33.679 --> 01:58:35.270
We're here. We got issues. We're all

01:58:35.280 --> 01:58:36.629
working through this, but we're here to

01:58:36.629 --> 01:58:36.639
pray.'And

01:58:36.639 --> 01:58:38.390
I see things, and the Lord

01:58:38.400 --> 01:58:39.430
shows me things,

01:58:39.440 --> 01:58:41.189
and I just try to make it as real as I

01:58:41.199 --> 01:58:42.550
can with y'all.

01:58:45.199 --> 01:58:46.790
Well, it's just that

01:58:46.800 --> 01:58:49.669
inadequacy, that feeling of when you're

01:58:49.679 --> 01:58:51.589
feeling like you're not good enough. And

01:58:51.599 --> 01:58:53.990
whenever it gets to where you

01:58:54.000 --> 01:58:56.229
hit the bottom and you say,

01:58:56.239 --> 01:58:58.070
'I can't do this.'And then he

01:58:58.080 --> 01:59:00.950
says, 'Thank you. You finally admitted

01:59:00.960 --> 01:59:01.830
you can't do

01:59:01.830 --> 01:59:01.840
this.'That's

01:59:01.840 --> 01:59:02.709
exactly what he said.

01:59:02.719 --> 01:59:04.229
And that's what happened. I

01:59:04.239 --> 01:59:06.470
said, 'I can't do this. I can't

01:59:06.480 --> 01:59:09.030
be enough. I'm not enough.'And he said,

01:59:09.040 --> 01:59:11.750
'You're right. You're not enough, Diana.

01:59:11.760 --> 01:59:14.390
You need me. It's not because you're

01:59:14.400 --> 01:59:17.270
good; it's because I'm good.'And so

01:59:17.280 --> 01:59:20.709
getting to that place and realizing

01:59:20.719 --> 01:59:23.589
that I'm not the victim. It's not about

01:59:23.599 --> 01:59:26.310
me. Stopping focusing on me and

01:59:26.320 --> 01:59:29.270
focusing on what God can do through me,

01:59:29.280 --> 01:59:33.030
and allowing that hurt to go away and

01:59:33.040 --> 01:59:34.709
just saying, 'No, I refuse to be the

01:59:34.719 --> 01:59:38.310
victim. I am not...

01:59:38.320 --> 01:59:40.149
what I have been through doesn't

01:59:40.159 --> 01:59:42.229
define me. It's what God can use and

01:59:42.239 --> 01:59:44.229
what I can yield to him, and he can flow

01:59:44.239 --> 01:59:47.109
through me.'Allowing me to be the

01:59:47.119 --> 01:59:48.950
best at what he's called me to be in

01:59:48.960 --> 01:59:51.189
this season and him pulling

01:59:51.199 --> 01:59:53.830
back those layers of me homeschooling my

01:59:53.840 --> 01:59:56.550
kids and saying, 'This is... you're doing

01:59:56.550 --> 01:59:56.560
this,'and

01:59:56.560 --> 01:59:58.870
seeing my kids flourish and

01:59:58.880 --> 02:00:03.189
grow, and seeing the joy.

02:00:03.199 --> 02:00:07.109
And just saying, 'You know what?

02:00:07.119 --> 02:00:08.390
It's not about

02:00:08.400 --> 02:00:10.709
this.

02:00:10.719 --> 02:00:12.149
It's just part of the chapter. It's just

02:00:12.159 --> 02:00:13.430
part of the book.

02:00:13.440 --> 02:00:15.030
It's not defining

02:00:15.030 --> 02:00:15.040
us.'It's

02:00:15.040 --> 02:00:17.589
focusing more on others

02:00:17.599 --> 02:00:19.830
because

02:00:19.840 --> 02:00:22.470
when you're focused so much on yourself,

02:00:22.480 --> 02:00:26.229
it tries to wedge a layer of pride and

02:00:26.239 --> 02:00:29.189
you don't even realize it because that

02:00:29.189 --> 02:00:29.199
woe-is-me

02:00:29.199 --> 02:00:32.229
mentality

02:00:32.239 --> 02:00:35.270
is also a form. It's a sneaky way

02:00:35.280 --> 02:00:37.750
that the enemy tries to get in and

02:00:37.760 --> 02:00:42.629
build pride.

02:00:42.639 --> 02:00:43.270
Sorry,

02:00:43.280 --> 02:00:44.470
I can't see your eyes very well.

02:00:44.480 --> 02:00:45.830
I don't have makeup on. It's late at

02:00:45.840 --> 02:00:49.830
night.

02:00:49.840 --> 02:00:54.629
I don't care about no makeup.

02:00:54.639 --> 02:00:57.030
Come on, cowgirl. I can't see them

02:00:57.040 --> 02:00:58.950
beautiful eyes. I'm trying to see you. I

02:00:58.960 --> 02:01:00.470
don't care if you don't have no makeup

02:01:00.480 --> 02:01:03.350
on. And they don't. I don't

02:01:03.360 --> 02:01:05.430
care. Whatever they think, whatever. But

02:01:05.440 --> 02:01:08.629
I feel like people need to

02:01:08.639 --> 02:01:10.070
hear more about your story.

02:01:10.080 --> 02:01:11.589
I feel like people need to know more

02:01:11.599 --> 02:01:13.830
about you. I know I talk a lot,

02:01:13.840 --> 02:01:15.350
but they never know. You're always the

02:01:15.360 --> 02:01:17.189
quiet one in the corner, but there's so

02:01:17.199 --> 02:01:19.270
much depth to you. And I feel like

02:01:19.280 --> 02:01:20.790
you're a gift to

02:01:20.790 --> 02:01:20.800
the people.

02:01:20.800 --> 02:01:23.510
People need to know

02:01:23.520 --> 02:01:25.990
that you've been through hell

02:01:26.000 --> 02:01:27.990
and

02:01:28.000 --> 02:01:29.830
you've not been burned. You have some

02:01:29.830 --> 02:01:29.840
go

02:01:29.840 --> 02:01:32.070
on. You struggle a little

02:01:32.070 --> 02:01:32.080
something,

02:01:32.080 --> 02:01:34.229
but you're still marching with me and we're

02:01:34.239 --> 02:01:34.950
still going in.

02:01:34.960 --> 02:01:37.350
The Lord kept me; it's the only

02:01:37.360 --> 02:01:38.470
reason I'm still here,

02:01:38.880 --> 02:01:39.750
truly.

02:01:41.119 --> 02:01:42.629
Because we pray

02:01:42.639 --> 02:01:44.790
and I believe it's

02:01:44.800 --> 02:01:46.870
the relationship that you've developed.

02:01:46.880 --> 02:01:49.109
They need to hear

02:01:49.119 --> 02:01:51.430
that even

02:01:51.440 --> 02:01:53.669
at the most of what we go through,

02:01:53.679 --> 02:01:55.030
we still have our stuff we're walking

02:01:55.040 --> 02:01:55.990
through. You still have your stuff

02:01:56.000 --> 02:01:57.589
you're walking through. Tell

02:01:57.589 --> 02:01:57.599
them

02:01:57.599 --> 02:01:59.830
we felt the inadequacy. I thought it

02:01:59.840 --> 02:02:01.030
was interesting because it went along

02:02:01.030 --> 02:02:01.040
with

02:02:01.040 --> 02:02:02.550
some of the conversations we've had.

02:02:02.560 --> 02:02:04.149
It doesn't go away; it's like you have

02:02:04.159 --> 02:02:05.910
to resist it. 'Resist the devil and he

02:02:05.920 --> 02:02:08.229
will flee.'If he knows your

02:02:08.239 --> 02:02:09.910
weakness and knows your history, he

02:02:09.920 --> 02:02:11.430
knows your past and he'll try to sneak

02:02:11.440 --> 02:02:12.870
in. You'll feel great and

02:02:12.880 --> 02:02:14.470
everything's great, the Lord's

02:02:14.480 --> 02:02:15.510
working through this and you feel like

02:02:15.520 --> 02:02:17.109
you've made so much progress, and then he

02:02:17.119 --> 02:02:19.030
just comes right in that one day and

02:02:19.040 --> 02:02:20.310
tries to knock you down. You say,

02:02:20.320 --> 02:02:22.629
'No, having done all to stand, stand

02:02:22.629 --> 02:02:22.639
therefore.'You

02:02:22.639 --> 02:02:25.430
get back up and you

02:02:25.440 --> 02:02:27.030
fight the good fight of faith, and it's

02:02:27.040 --> 02:02:29.109
just keeping on going and not letting

02:02:29.119 --> 02:02:31.350
that derail you because we are soldiers for

02:02:31.360 --> 02:02:33.189
Christ. We're marching on. We're doing

02:02:33.199 --> 02:02:34.950
this for the

02:02:34.960 --> 02:02:36.950
kingdom. We

02:02:36.960 --> 02:02:39.030
have a job to do. No matter how

02:02:39.040 --> 02:02:40.790
seemingly insignificant you may feel

02:02:40.800 --> 02:02:43.109
that it is, even if it's just

02:02:43.119 --> 02:02:45.430
raising your children, you're

02:02:45.430 --> 02:02:45.440
being

02:02:45.440 --> 02:02:48.149
very effective.

02:02:48.159 --> 02:02:50.629
That

02:02:50.639 --> 02:02:53.030
is one of the most important jobs you

02:02:53.040 --> 02:02:55.270
can do, and being a good spouse.

02:02:55.280 --> 02:02:58.390
As women and wives, we are called to

02:02:58.400 --> 02:03:01.350
be the helpmate. He made us to be

02:03:01.360 --> 02:03:03.910
a helpmate to support our husbands,

02:03:03.920 --> 02:03:06.709
to uplift them, pray for them,

02:03:06.719 --> 02:03:09.510
extol them, and

02:03:09.520 --> 02:03:11.910
support them in everything.

02:03:11.920 --> 02:03:14.070
I think a lot of times, even with women,

02:03:14.080 --> 02:03:16.229
it's gotten out of control with the

02:03:16.239 --> 02:03:20.149
whole girl power 'hear me

02:03:20.149 --> 02:03:20.159
roar'thing.

02:03:20.159 --> 02:03:22.149
It's like getting back to the basics:

02:03:22.159 --> 02:03:24.790
we're here to raise our

02:03:24.800 --> 02:03:27.830
families, be that support,

02:03:27.840 --> 02:03:30.390
and let Him use us in the way that He

02:03:30.400 --> 02:03:32.229
wants to use us—not what we think we

02:03:32.239 --> 02:03:34.950
should do, but what He wants us to do,

02:03:34.960 --> 02:03:37.109
being His hands, His feet, and a

02:03:37.119 --> 02:03:37.750
vessel.

02:03:37.760 --> 02:03:39.109
I totally support you doing

02:03:39.119 --> 02:03:39.589
anything.

02:03:40.320 --> 02:03:41.990
I'm never that husband who says, 'You need to

02:03:42.000 --> 02:03:43.910
be a submissive

02:03:43.910 --> 02:03:43.920
wife.'I've

02:03:43.920 --> 02:03:46.390
always said, 'Come out of that

02:03:46.390 --> 02:03:46.400
box.'There's

02:03:46.400 --> 02:03:47.990
so much you can offer because

02:03:48.000 --> 02:03:50.870
she counsels me all the time and helps

02:03:50.880 --> 02:03:52.950
me get through this; she has so much

02:03:52.960 --> 02:03:55.510
wisdom inside of her. Even when

02:03:55.520 --> 02:03:57.109
she's doing this, this is nothing

02:03:57.119 --> 02:03:58.550
compared to what I hear all the time.

02:03:58.560 --> 02:04:01.030
She really has helped me, but I

02:04:01.040 --> 02:04:04.229
feel there's so many people that

02:04:06.400 --> 02:04:07.430
need to hear it.

02:04:07.440 --> 02:04:10.870
Well,

02:04:10.880 --> 02:04:14.870
I just think it's

02:04:14.880 --> 02:04:19.030
going back to the basics of the ABCs

02:04:19.040 --> 02:04:21.350
of faith, or even just

02:04:21.360 --> 02:04:24.310
talking about how it's not the Leave it to

02:04:24.310 --> 02:04:24.320
Beaver thing

02:04:24.320 --> 02:04:26.070
because

02:04:26.080 --> 02:04:28.950
I don't cook.

02:04:28.960 --> 02:04:31.669
I am a terrible

02:04:31.679 --> 02:04:34.709
cook. I grew up on

